%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2331","headword_ar":"اَبْرَقُ","root":"brq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A rope ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habol","text_ar":"حَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having two colours;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twisted with a black strand and a white strand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) and in like manner, (JK,) a mountain ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabal","text_ar":"جَبَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", JK, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are two colours,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black and white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and (so in the S , but in the K “ or,”) anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having blackness and whiteness together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayosN A^aboraqN","text_ar":"تَيْسٌ اَبْرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanozN baroqaA='u","text_ar":"عَنْزٌ بَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black and white he-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN baroqaA='u","text_ar":"شَاةٌ بَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ewe whose white wool is cleft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divided, by black flocks"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraqu","text_ar":"اَبْرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqaA='u","text_ar":"بَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to sheep or goats are like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolaqu","text_ar":"اَبْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloqaA='u","text_ar":"بَلْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to beasts of the equine kind, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaEu","text_ar":"اَبْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqoEaA='u","text_ar":"بَقْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to dogs. (Lh, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqaA='u","text_ar":"بَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name given to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M;) because it has blackness and whiteness mingled in it: (M, TA:) dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqaAwaAni","text_ar":"بَرْقَاوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN baroqaA='u","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ بَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eye black in the iris, with whiteness [of the rest] of the bulb."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoDapN baroqA='u","text_ar":"رَوْضَةٌ بَرْقا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A meadorc,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden, in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":192},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are two colours."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroqapN","text_ar":"بُرْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". in seven places. ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraqu","text_ar":"اَبْرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Tekmileh, K.) ―         -b6-  And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroqN","text_ar":"بُرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a name for The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"locusts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crickets, termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAdib","text_ar":"جَنَادِب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IB, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain Persian medicine, good for the memory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","K","TA","S","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}